      "title": "Real-Time Detection of the Environment Features in Infrastructure Construction Sites Based on Enhanced 
YOLOv8",
      "abstract": "Real-time detection of environmental features on infrastructure construction sites is crucial, espec
ially for monitoring the safety equipment usage of construction workers. To adapt to different construction sites and i
mprove detection efficiency, this paper designs a recognition method based on images collected by Unmanned Aerial Vehic
les (UAVs). However, recognizing safety compliance in UAV-captured images presents significant challenges due to the sm
all size of workers and complex backgrounds. To address these issues, this paper proposes a novel recognition framework
 based on YOLOv8, named YOLOv8Enhanced (YOLOv8-E). The proposed model introduces HGStem and HGBlock into the feature ex
traction module of YOLOv8 and redesigns the feature fusion layer structure to improve the detection of small targets. A
dditionally, the VoVGSCSP module is incorporated to replace the conventional C2F module, enhancing feature representati
on while reducing computational complexity. Experimental results demonstrate that YOLOv8-E achieves a mAP{@}50 of 0.85 
and a Precision (P) of 0.90, showing significant performance improvements over existing models. These findings confirm 
the effectiveness of YOLOv8-E in accurately identifying the safety equipment wearing status of workers in UAV-captured 
images of construction sites.",
