    {
      "title": "A Lightweight Vehicle Detection Model for Complex Traffic Scenarios",
      "abstract": "With the development of autonomous driving, the detection of pedestrians and vehicles in complex sce
nes has been challenged by the problems of misdetection, omission and high model complexity. In order to overcome these
 problems, a novel lightweight target detection algorithm PCA-YOLO is proposed based on YOLO11 in this study. Firstly, 
partial convolution is integrated into the backbone network, and the C3k2 module is improved into the P_C3k2 structure,
 which can efficiently extract spatial features while reducing the number of model parameters and computational overhea
d. Secondly, a lightweight upsampling operator are added to the neck structure to better capture target information; me
anwhile, the adaptive spatial feature fusion module is embedded into the object detector head, which effectively filter
s out conflicting information. Finally, experimental outcomes on the KITTI dataset show that the model PCA-YOLO can att
ain higher detection accuracy when compared against YOLO11n and other baseline algorithms, with varying degrees of mode
l size, parameter count, and complexity reduction.",
      "year": 2026,
      "venue": "2026 International Conference on Communication Networks and Machine Learning (CNML)",
      "citation_count": 0,
      "doi": "10.1109/CNML68938.2026.11452532",
