      "source": "semantic_scholar",
      "expanded_from_seed": "A Real-Time Apple Targets Detection Method for Picking Robot Based on Improved YOLOv5"
    },
    {
      "title": "A Lightweight Network Based on Multi-Attention Mechanisms for Metal Surface Defect Detection",
      "abstract": "Defect detection is a crucial part in the manufacturing process of industrial products. The processi
ng of metal work pieces places higher demands on the accuracy and robustness of defect detection methods. However, curr
ent surface defect detection methods for metal materials face challenges such as a wide variety of defect types, extrem
ely small defect area sizes, and high similarity between defects and the background. This paper proposes a high-perform
ance metal surface defect detection method to address these issues. First, this paper proposes a network with multi-att
ention mechanisms, which has training parameters of only 1.77M. Second, the public steel dataset are improved in this p
aper, named Modified_steel dataset. Third, this article conducts validation experiments on the steel, Modified_steel an
d Northeastern University Surface Defect Detection Database, proving the effectiveness of our proposed method. Finally,
 the inference time of network is 1.4ms per image, with an average precision of 99.1% at the intersection over union th
reshold of 0.5. Ablation experiments show that the network outperforms lightweight networks in the You Look Only Once s
eries in both inference time and accuracy, demonstrating the effectiveness and practical significance of our method. Th
e code is available in https://github.com/Xuejiao-Zhang/MAM_Net.",
