    {
      "title": "Advanced Deep Learning for Early Detection and Classification of Guava Diseases",
      "abstract": "Guava (Psidium guajava) is one of the most edible tropical and subtropical fruits worldwide and hold
s a substantial economic importance. Guava cultivation faces challenges due to various diseases affecting the leaves an
d trees of the fruit, such as anthracnose, canker, rust, and fruit fly infestations. These diseases cause yield losses 
of up to 30% to 40% annually. Therefore, these diseases should be detected and addressed as early as possible. This art
icle discusses various CNN-based automated systems for early detection and classification of guava diseases using trans
fer and hybrid deep learning approaches. The datasets primarily used for detecting guava diseases have also been discus
sed in the article. The deep learning-based techniques have accurately identified guava leaf and fruit diseases with an
 accuracy score of 90-99%. Thus, these techniques are beneficial and proficient in the early detection of diseases in g
uava fruit and leaves.",
