    {
      "title": "ReLAD: Retrieval-Augmented LAtent Diffusion for Complex Aerial Image Generation",
      "abstract": "While significant advances have been made in text-to-image synthesis using diffusion models, the gen
eration of aerial images remains less explored. Direct application of diffusion models to aerial imagery is challenging
 due to the unique characteristics of aerial datasets, including small but high-density objects, the scarcity of text-a
erial image datasets, and the poor data distribution. To address these challenges, this paper proposes ReLAD, which imp
lements a Retrieval-augmented LAtent Diffusion model for complex aerial image generation, tailored for high-resolution 
aerial imagery in text-to-image synthesis. ReLAD proceeds with four key components: retrieval-augmented representation 
learning, text synthesis, latent diffusion optimization, and text-guided aerial image generation. We validate the stren
gth of our proposed framework by generating realistic and complex aerial images, demonstrating its capability to produc
e clear images even under high-noise, severe nighttime conditions. Experimental results demonstrate that our model achi
eves an FID score of 92.11, outperforming the average of baselines by 45.4 points and showing a significant improvement
 compared to Stable Diffusion and other conditional models. This paper is the first to generate aerial data from textua
l insights, opening new avenues for aerial imaging research and applications.",
